oc:kn_07f7dce9 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing typewriter text animations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use per-character opacity for typewriter effects. Always use string slicing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Per-character opacity requires rendering all characters with individual opacity values, which is more complex, less performant, and less faithful to a true typewriter effect than simply slicing the visible portion of the string." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_504d08f9 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any typewriter-style text reveal" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "tsx" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use useCurrentFrame() to drive the string slice index: `fullText.slice(0, Math.floor(frame / charFrames))` where charFrames controls typing speed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "String slicing based on frame count is the canonical Remotion approach for character-by-character text reveal." .

oc:kn_7ec9898b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring typewriter animation timing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use 2 frames per character as a baseline typing speed and 16 frames for cursor blink cycle at standard FPS." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These values produce a natural-feeling typing speed and cursor blink at common video frame rates (24-30fps)." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b03c2f7b a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing typewriter effects with natural pacing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Add a mid-typing pause by detecting when a pause phrase has been fully typed, then freezing the slice index for a calculated number of pause frames before resuming." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A pause after a sentence makes the animation feel more natural and readable, mimicking real human typing cadence." .

oc:kn_f57a90e3 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a highlighter-pen word highlight animation" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "tsx" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use spring() with high damping (e.g., damping: 200) to drive a scaleX transform from 0 to 1 on an absolutely-positioned highlight span behind the target word, with transformOrigin: 'left center'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The spring animation with scaleX gives a smooth wipe-on effect that looks like a highlighter being drawn across a word." .

